$interpreted: Tica: TADA~ Tica's back, mission accomplished!
Charle: What took you so long?
Tica: Actually um, I went the long way and stopped by Atlas...
Charle: What were you doing there?!
Tica: A-A-Adventure?
Charle: Who permitted you to go alone?!
Tica: I fixed a lot of problems... all by myself! Neat, ain't it?
Charle: It's dangerous! How many times do I have to tell you!?
Tica: Alright. I won't wander off alone again, I promise~
Tica: But... I've made some new discoveries on this trip. Would Headmaster be willing to listen?
Charle: ...*sigh*....speak.
Tica: In Atlas, I saw a rune puppet with a black aura...
Tica: Headmaster please, PLEASE let me finish!
Charle: Continue.

Tica: After getting the package, there was another cloaked stranger emitting a black aura that was using arcane magic. 
Does Headmaster know who that might be?
Charle: Black aura...
Charle: It's none of your business. Next time you're in danger, just run like hell. Don't let your curiosity kill you.
Tica: Eh? Headmaster, you sneaky devil, you~
Charle: Nothing else to mention? I need to deal with Clovis' package.
Tica: What does it say?
Charle: You have a new mission.
Charle: Please go to Whistlewood Valley and bring back the same seed.
Tica: What? Another trip?!
Charle: You don't like going to class, do you?
Tica: Wait! Headmaster Ceres, where are you going?
Charle: The Kingdom of the Sun.
Charle: The Soul Energy extraction device for the Dragoneye Gem is almost complete. I have much work to do.
Tica: But you didn't tell me where the seed is?
Charle: I don't know either, otherwise why I would I appoint you to this mission? Good luck!
Tica: Oh well, I'm sure it'll show up. Ready, set, go go go!
